Trump’s Las Vegas hotel has not.
"All Las Vegas hotels have donated food and rooms for emergency personnel except for one: Trump International Hotel Las Vegas," a Facebook post claimed.
Not the only exceptionUnlike some other hotel groups operating in Las Vegas, Trump’s hotel did not donate rooms, food or supplies, according to reporting by us and other media.
Las Vegas is the nation’s largest hotel market, with roughly 150,000 rooms and thousands more under construction, according to the Las Vegas Review-Journal.
Since then, several hotel groups operating in Las Vegas have announced donations of hotel rooms, food and supplies for workers dealing with the health crisis.